<span class="avatar"><img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/af175322f36eab65a1d3408dbfc919ac?s=40&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.melskitchencafe.com%2Fwp-includes%2Fimages%2Fblank.gif&amp;r=G' class='avatar avatar-40 photo' height='40' width='40' /></span>
<span class="comment_num"><a href="#comment-69621" title="Permalink to this comment" rel="nofollow">59</a></span>
<span class="comment_author">Michelle</span>
<span class="comment_time">December 21, 2011 at 9:30 am</span>

					</dt>
					<dd class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
<div class="format_text" id="comment-body-69621">
<p>Does it matter if you use a non-stick pan or not?  I made it but when I poured it out all of the little brown bits came off and into my caramel as well.</p>
</div>
					</dd>
					<dt class="comment byuser comment-author-admin bypostauthor odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-69627">
<span class="avatar"><a href="http://www.melskitchencafe.com" rel="nofollow"><img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/f3b96974ca95ad69b3a89992c88c13ee?s=40&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.melskitchencafe.com%2Fwp-includes%2Fimages%2Fblank.gif&amp;r=G' class='avatar avatar-40 photo' height='40' width='40' /></a></span>
<span class="comment_num"><a href="#comment-69627" title="Permalink to this comment" rel="nofollow">60</a></span>
<span class="comment_author"><a href='http://www.melskitchencafe.com' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Mel</a></span>
<span class="comment_time">December 21, 2011 at 10:03 am</span>

					</dt>
					<dd class="comment byuser comment-author-admin bypostauthor odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
<div class="format_text" id="comment-body-69627">
<p>Michelle &#8211; the best pans to use for caramel and other candy making are stainless steel heavy bottomed pans. I&#8217;ve never used a nonstick but I can see how that might have caused the issue you described. Sorry about that! Hopefully the caramels were still salvageable.</p>
</div>
					</dd>
					<dt class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-81255">
